                    "company": "Eindhoven University of Technology",
                    "description": "Research focus: Unsupervised Domain Adaptation and Generalization\n\nIn the conventional training of a neural network, we rely on labeled datasets to facilitate supervised learning. However, when aiming to deploy such a model in a different context where labeled data is scarce or absent, its performance experiences a significant decline, rendering it impractical for real-world applications.\n\nThe essence of Unsupervised Domain Adaptation and Generalization lies in equipping the model to acquire domain-independent insights that retain significance and relevance across varying contexts. This is accomplished by extending the model's training regimen beyond annotated data from a source domain, to include adaptations that enable it to glean knowledge from datasets with lack of labels.\n\nThe outcome of this approach yields a model that exhibits superior performance compared to one exclusively trained on labeled datasets. The resultant adaptability renders a model operationally viable for real-world deployment, thus representing a valuable asset in practical scenarios.\n\nMy professional focus centers on facilitating this intricate process, thereby enhancing the efficacy of neural networks in diverse and dynamic scenarios encountered within everyday life.\n\nKey Achievements:\n- Formulated and implemented novel Unsupervised Domain Adaptation techniques.\n- Demonstrated improved model performance through domain-invariant feature learning.\n- Daily utilization of TensorFlow and PyTorch to drive experimentation and innovation.\n- Guided and mentored Bachelor's and Master's students, facilitating their project success.\n- Coaching role at TU/e Honors Academy 2020, nurturing future talent.\n- Instructed at Advanced Deep Learning course, empowering students in cutting-edge techniques.",
                    "title": "PhD Candidate",
                    "employment_type": "Full-time"
                }
            ]
